article.description: Denver's late run tops Western Illinois 75-67
article.headline: Denver's late run tops Western Illinois 75-67
article.linkText: Denver's late run tops Western Illinois 75-67
article.story: DENVER -- Chris Udofia scored 21 points, gathered eight rebounds and had seven assists and Denver used a 12-5 run late to top Western Illinois 75-67 on Thursday. With the teams tied at 62 and 4:08 left in the game, the Pioneers scored 10 of the next 14 points -- including five from Chris Udofia and a trey by Brett Olson -- then made 3 of 4 free throws inside of 46 seconds to escape with the win. Denver (14-12, 7-4) led by three at the half. The Pioneers shot 66 percent, including 9 of 14 from beyond the arc. Bryant Rucker had 17 points, Cam Griffin added 15 and Nate Engesser came off the bench for 11 points. Garret Covington led Western Illinois (9-17, 3-8 Summit) with 18 points. Michael Ochereobia had 14 points with eight boards, Jabari Sandifer added 13 and Adam Link chipped in 12.
